items.title: How hard will JLR’s pause on US exports hit Tata Motors?
items.description: A bumpy road ahead for JLR with revenue and earnings cuts in the near-term seen given the need to rework trade terms with the US market

items.title: VVIP Infratech gets new government contracts worth Rs 414 crore
items.description: The contracts include a Rs 175 crore sewerage network project in Rishikesh under the Ganga Rejuvenation Mission, funded by German Development Bank (GIZ), and a Rs 238 crore power distribution initiative across key Uttar Pradesh districts

items.title: Apple, Samsung may take India route for exports to beat US' wall of tariffs against China: Report
items.description: Trump announced a 34 percent tariff on Chinese goods, over and above the earlier duties, and 26 percent on goods shipped from India
